<dl id="n10071i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10071i">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10071i"> 71(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Rohrpost / wrapper / band</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Pour les lettres ordinaires exp&eacute;di&eacute;es, il existe des <mark>bandes</mark> timbr&eacute;es; en outre, des cartes sp&eacute;ciales en carton rose sont vendues sans augmentation dans tous les bureaux de postes et t&eacute;l&eacute;graphes, etc., de Berlin. Les lettres et cartes postales affranchies doivent porter simplement la mention <mark>Rohrpost</mark> sur le c&ocirc;t&eacute; gauche de l&apos;adresse <font color="green">[For ordinary dispatched letters, there are stamped bands; moreover special cards in pink cardboard are sold without surcharge at all post offices, telegraph offices and so on in Berlin. Stamped letters and post cards only need to bear the word <i>Rohrpost</i> to the left of the address]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 346</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01035d" href="c01all.htm#c01035d">VI.C.01:035(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
